title: Gnomish Ranger quest
data:
The **Gnomish Ranger Quest** is a revival of the [defunct](/wiki/Defunct_features "Defunct features") [Gnome quest](/wiki/Gnome_quest "Gnome quest"). It sees Gnomish Rangers challenge the [Great High Shaman of Kurtulmak](/wiki/Great_High_Shaman_of_Kurtulmak "Great High Shaman of Kurtulmak") for [The Rogue Gear-spirits](/wiki/DNetHack_artifacts#The_Rogue_Gear-spirits "DNetHack artifacts"). For more information on the quest [branch](/wiki/Branch "Branch") in general, see the [quest](/wiki/Quest "Quest") article.

This quest is tightly tied to the [Gnomish mines](/wiki/Gnomish_mines "Gnomish mines"). All holes and trap doors in the mines lead to the Home level, and the upstair on the Home level leads to [Minetown](/wiki/Minetown "Minetown"). The quest portal still links to the Dungeons of Doom at the usual depth.

Gnomes of at least 6th level will be accepted on the quest, and at that point they are likely to be able to complete it, as well. At least 20 alignment is still required, however.

The main quest enemies are kobolds, though the occasional [i](/wiki/I "I") spawns as well. Sometimes a [giant spider](/wiki/Giant_spider "Giant spider") may generate guarding a web trap.

**Ruggo the Gnome King** is located on the throne; however, he is no longer the quest leader. Instead, the **damaged Arcadian Avenger** is the quest leader. She is hidden in the closet behind Ruggo's throne.

The downstair and portal are located randomly in the maze of corridors, the marked upstair leads to a random spot in [Minetown](/wiki/Minetown "Minetown"). Until the quest is completed, the upstair is partially collapsed, and the character will not be able to squeeze up it if they are burdened.

### Upper filler level(s)

This is a Mines-style level. Indeed, these levels are almost identical to mines levels, down to the guaranteed random tool.

Gnomish Ranger quest

From NetHackWiki
Jump to navigation Jump to search

The Gnomish Ranger Quest is a revival of the defunct Gnome quest. It sees Gnomish Rangers challenge the Great High Shaman of Kurtulmak for The Rogue Gear-spirits. For more information on the quest branch in general, see the quest article.

This quest is tightly tied to the Gnomish mines. All holes and trap doors in the mines lead to the Home level, and the upstair on the Home level leads to Minetown. The quest portal still links to the Dungeons of Doom at the usual depth.

Gnomes of at least 6th level will be accepted on the quest, and at that point they are likely to be able to complete it, as well. At least 20 alignment is still required, however.

The main quest enemies are kobolds, though the occasional i spawns as well. Sometimes a giant spider may generate guarding a web trap.
